==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humiliate
<hw>Hu*mil"i*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Humiliated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Humiliating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>humiliatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>humiliare</ets>. See
<er>Humble</er>.]</ety> <def>To reduce to a lower position in one's own
eyes, or in the eyes of others; to cause a loss of pride or dignity; to
humble; to mortify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We stand <qex>humiliated</qex> rather than encouraged.</q>
<rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>humiliated</ent>⟦br⟧
